                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d118">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/3892: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gilbert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-03-09T09:00:00+01:00"
                            >March 9, 1936—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 9:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>81. The Italian reply addressed to the Chairman of the Committee of Thirteen
                    states “the Italian Government, in response to the appeal addressed to it,
                    agrees in principle to the opening of negotiations concerning the settlement of
                    the Italo-Abyssinian conflict”.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gilbert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
